    summary: "India officially surpassed Japan to become the world's fourth-largest economy by nominal GDP in early 2025, with GDP projected at approximately $4.34 trillion.",
    content: "According to the International Monetary Fund's (IMF) World Economic Outlook update released in early 2025, India overtook Japan to become the world's fourth-largest economy by nominal GDP, behind only the United States, China, and Germany. India's nominal GDP for 2025 was projected at approximately $4.34 trillion, marginally surpassing Japan's $4.31 trillion. India is now expected to overtake Germany to become the third-largest economy by 2027-28. The milestone reflects India's sustained 6-7% annual growth rate, services-led recovery, and the Modi government's infrastructure push. NITI Aayog and the Finance Ministry projected India to become a $5 trillion economy by 2026-27 and a $30+ trillion developed economy by 2047. India remains the fastest-growing major economy for the fourth consecutive year.",
