    summary: "The Assam government, in January 2025, reaffirmed its commitment to implement Clause 6 of the Assam Accord 1985, providing safeguards for the cultural, social, and linguistic identity of the Assamese people.",
    content: "The Assam government reaffirmed its commitment in January 2025 to implement Clause 6 of the Assam Accord 1985, which promises constitutional, legislative, and administrative safeguards to protect the cultural, social, and linguistic identity of the Assamese people. The move came amid ongoing demands from civil society groups including AASU (All Assam Students' Union) and Asam Jatiyatabadi Yuba Chatra Parishad (AJYCP). The Justice (retd) Biplab Kumar Sharma Committee, formed in 2019, had recommended 1951 as the cut-off year for defining 'Assamese' (instead of 1971 as in the Citizenship Amendment Act). The Assam Cabinet approved reservations of up to 100% in Group III/IV state government jobs and 80% in Group I/II for Assamese people, and 19% of land to be reserved for indigenous communities in revenue circles. The implementation roadmap was targeted for completion by 2026.",
